      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 35: Plain-text stripping trims leading/trailing whitespace and newlines from the whole message. That changes user-authored message content in conversation previews, reply snippets, accessibility text, and notifications whenever any renderable markdown is present. Preserve the original outer whitespace semantics, or only trim syntax-owned newlines from fenced-code bodies. Suggested fix: return `text` directly here instead of `text.trimmingCharacters(in: .whitespacesAndNewlines)`.",
