      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 209: Markdown link parsing only extracts the raw substring between \u0027(\u0027 and \u0027)\u0027. Markdown also allows optional titles and whitespace, e.g. `[x](https://example.com \"title\")`; this makes `URL(string:)` fail and `containsDisallowedMarkdownLink` disables rich rendering for otherwise valid safe links, while `stripMarkdownLinks` also leaves them unstripped in previews/notifications. Parse the destination according to Markdown syntax before validating it, or delegate link validation to the parsed AttributedString runs. Example fix:\n```suggestion\nlet destination \u003d String(text[urlStart..\u003curlEnd])\n    .trimmingCharacters(in: .whitespacesAndNewlines)\n    .split(whereSeparator: { $0 \u003d\u003d \" \" || $0 \u003d\u003d \"\\t\" })\n    .first\n    .map(String.init)\nguard let destination else { return nil }\nreturn URL(string: destination)\n```",
      "revId": "71d044b71d73b4f992eec2398eb36eee724884fe",
